might be a null ptr if we serialize a model with zero buffers size(e.g.

This commit relaxs the "buffers" null ptr checking for this situation,
and also updates the "subgraphs" checking for null ptr dereference.

The following dirs (which are soft-links really) will removed in a (near) future ROCm release. This commit updates `rocm_configure.bzl` to account for that change by explicitly copying over the header files (for `local_config_rocm` repo) from the following directories instead
* $ROCM_PATH/hiprand/include
* $ROCM_PATH/rocrand/include

Unfortunately making the above change also breaks the build, if the directories that will be going away, are still present. This is because we end up with two `make_copy_dir_rule`s in `rocm_configure.bzl` that try to write to the same destination dirs

```

```

[{"sha":"99487be319ca212504742c7b1eeaebaaf71182ae","author":{"name":"Chuanhao Zhuge","email":"2df560f87cba785bae78536bb6567a32ee2f9ce7@google.com"},"message":"Allow configure logical cpu devices after context is initialized.

To configure logical cpu devices, user should either use tf.config.set_logical_device_configuration() before context initialization or use the newly introduced tf.context.context().add_logical_cpu_devices() after context is initialized.

EagerContext's local_device_mgr is changed to use DynamicDeviceMgr to allow adding device after initialization.

Changes in DynamicDeviceMgr:
- Add a constructor that allows taking a list of devices at construction.
- Use vector instead of map to own the devices. This is because there are use cases that require ListDevices() produces the same order as the list of devices being passed in.

[{"sha":"cb7f144b577a92d655d8f8c0243219c1dab7dab3","author":{"name":"Nick Felt","email":"e1c8e592cc7cfe6a58425c8d09efbf61173fd491@google.com"},"message":"Pull legacy contrib behavior out of ResourceSummaryWriter

This refactors ResourceSummaryWriter to remove the `v2` parameter, which previously controlled whether the behavior reflected `create_summary_writer()`, aka the legacy tf.contrib.summary API, or `create_summary_writer_v2()`, the API exposed in TF 2. Instead, we just split the behavior into two distinct implementations, `_LegacyResourceSummaryWriter` for contrib and `_ResourceSummaryWriter` for TF 2. This makes each implementation simpler to read in advance of further changes to this class hierarchy.

The symbols have been given leading underscores to discourage their direct usage (since users should refer to the `SummaryWriter` interface only), and I've updated `NoopSummaryWriter` to `_NoopSummaryWriter` accordingly.
